Wrap a measuring tape around your head, locate the tape above your ears and keep the tape level front to back (from just above your brow ridge to the lower crest of your occipital bone). Take the measurement and match it to the helmet sizing guid below.

How To Fit A Helmet

Measure and find your size helmet
Adjust the fit using the helmet internal fit system
Adjust chinstrap and buckle
Adjust the interior pads

Positioning

Position the helmet low enough in the front to protect the forehead and not leave a goggle gaper gap (gorbie gap), but not too low that goggles push down on the nose

*Note: Chinstrap buckle should be fastened and the strap pulled snugly before riding.

