THE GIRO UNION MIPS HELMET

The all-new Union MIPS comes fully loaded for all mountain freeriding and resort exploration. In-Mold Construction and adjustable venting create a lighter, cooler helmet making the Union MIPS ideal for both ascending and descending the slopes. Go the distance in comfort with XT2 anti-odor protection and the adjustable In Form Fit System. And rest easy knowing that the Multi-directional Impact Protection System (MIPS) can provide more protection in certain impacts.The Giro Union MIPS Features:
• MIPS – Multi-directional Impact Protection System
• In-Mold Construction
• In Form Fit System
• Vertical Tuning
• Thermostat Control Adjustable Venting
• Super Cool Vents
• Stack Ventilation
• XT2 Anti-Odor Protection
• Compatible With Aftermarket Giro Audio Systems by Outdoor Tech
• Seamless Compatibility With All Giro Goggles
•Compliance: CE EN1077
• S (52–55.5cm), M (55.5-59cm), L (59-62.5cm)

 


 How To Measure Your Head For A Helmet

Wrap a measuring tape around your head, locate the tape above your ears and keep the tape level front to back (from just above your brow ridge to the lower crest of your occipital bone). Take the measurement and match it to the helmet sizing guid below.

How To Fit A Helmet

Measure and find your size helmet
Adjust the fit using the helmet internal fit system
Adjust chinstrap and buckle
Adjust the interior pads

Positioning

Position the helmet low enough in the front to protect the forehead and not leave a goggle gaper gap (gorbie gap), but not too low that goggles push down on the nose

*Note: Chinstrap buckle should be fastened and the strap pulled snugly before riding.

